                <li><strong>“If I use video chat, I’m automatically safer.”</strong> — Not necessarily. Video can still be recorded without your consent. Stick to platforms that prohibit recording and allow you to report violations.</li>
                <li><strong>“Anonymous chat is completely risk‑free.”</strong> — Anonymous ≠ invincible. Malware, phishing links, and screen recording remain threats. Always use common sense.</li>
                <li><strong>“Young people are the only ones at risk.”</strong> — Anyone can be targeted. Adults fall for romance scams and phishing just as often as teenagers face bullying.</li>
            </ol>
            <p>Real safety comes from <strong>informed behaviour</strong>, not avoiding technology altogether.</p>

